Substitute Odenyi levelled the score for Tusker in the 71st minute when he beat goalkeeper Katasi with a low shot to the right side of the goalpost. 

The hosts piled the pressure in search of a winner and in the 82nd minute, their efforts paid off when Meja headed home from a rebound. 

It was his eighth strike of the seaon and he is now two behind second placed Elvis Rupia of AFC Leopards and five behind leader Eric Kapaito of Kariobangi Sharks in the top scorers chart. Benjamin Mosha starred for the Dockers as he grabbed a brace. High-flying Wazito have a date with 2008 champions Mathare United. He says the President's support for the Sh4.5 billion car grant contributed to the outcome. Opposition says the result is an "electoral holdup" and urges the public to protest against it. Somalia, facing an electoral impasse, has seen cases of Covid-19 rise significantly this month.